## Description
The **Pweb template&nbsp;**resource&nbsp;allows to manage Pweb assets. You can use this resource in workflow tasks that produce Pwebs.

## Additional creation parameters
None.

## Resource editor
None.

> Note

For more information, see: [Pweb](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/pweb).

## Release parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Section

Field

Description

**Configuration**

**Summary**

Brief description of the release

**Assets**

**Bundle**

Select and upload the Pweb file in ZIP format.

## Deploy parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Section

Field

Description

**Configuration**

**Release**

Select a&nbsp;**Release **of the resource from the drop-down menu.

**Tenant**

Select the&nbsp;**Tenant**&nbsp;on which you want to deploy the resource from the drop-down menu.

**Server**

**Custom Domain**

*(optional)&nbsp;*Enter a custom domain to distribute the Pweb. If empty, the default domain will be used.

> Note

If a deploy of a Pweb template resource is already enabled on a tenant, the value of this field is automatically populated with the previously configured custom domain.

**Custom domain for Short URL**

Enter the custom domain to use for the short URL.

> Note

This field is only visible if the **Short URL** option is selected.

**GA tracking id**

Google Analytics identifier, used to identify the campaign

**Analytics**

Enable Analytics tracking.

**Anonymization**

Enable anonymization of Analytics data.

> Tip

Click **Publish **to publish the release on the tenant.

Click **Deploy** to publish and enable the release on the tenant.
